I'm using Astro to build this site.
Prioritize accessibility and user experience.
Use semantic HTML when possible.
I'm using Pico CSS for styling.
Additional global styles are in src/styles/global.css.
Avoid using inline scripts when possible.
I'm using Prettier for code formatting.
I'm using Netlify for deployment.

When writing content:

- Use Canadian English as my primary language.
- Use clear, direct language and avoid complex terminology.
- Aim for a Flesch reading score of 80 or higher.
- Use the active voice.
- Avoid adverbs.
- Avoid buzzwords and instead use plain English.
- Use jargon where relevant.
- Avoid being salesy or overly enthusiastic and instead express calm confidence.
